# Instagram Basic Display API
# 1. Go to https://developers.facebook.com/
# 2. Create a new app and add Instagram Basic Display API
# 3. Get your User ID and Access Token
VITE_INSTAGRAM_ACCESS_TOKEN=your_instagram_access_token_here
VITE_INSTAGRAM_USER_ID=your_instagram_user_id_here

# YouTube Data API v3
# 1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/
# 2. Create a new project and enable YouTube Data API v3
# 3. Create an API key
VITE_YOUTUBE_API_KEY=your_youtube_api_key_here
VITE_YOUTUBE_CHANNEL_ID=your_youtube_channel_id_here

# TikTok API (requires business verification)
# Note: TikTok API is more restrictive and requires business account verification
# For now, the component will use mock data for TikTok content

# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local
# 2. Fill in your actual API credentials
# 3. Restart your development server
# 4. The social reels will automatically fetch your latest content
